value.0: The sarcophagus' heavy lid is fashioned from unadorned stone. It is a tomb of a warrior.
This plate armor of Abiz is very old. It is also ruined and useless. It still retains an aura of power. It is embossed with dragons long dead and skeletal.
Whether for good or ill, some creature lies here, long undisturbed.
This ancient tomb radiates evil intent. Some monstrous being long corrupted must be buried within.

A wise and powerful bard in the wastes of the deserts created these instruments, using them to test and reward the students of his bardic temple to the god Horus-Re.

These pipes can call forth mighty power if played correctly by a extremely talented bard.
